text: Gonnosfanadiga (Gònnos) is a town and comune (municipality) in the Province of Sud Sardegna in Sardinia, Italy. As of 2016, 6,611 people lived there. Its area is 125.19 km². It is 180 meters above sea level. == References == == Other websites == Category:Communes of the Province of South Sardinia
